"{\"uid\": \"www.huffingtonpost.com.-adst-before-brexit-brentrance-b-10715582-html-Part4\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"that I have more or less just stated.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 37, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The focus that I remember was on whether Britain would decide to join.\", \"from\": 38, \"to\": 108, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think it was pretty well decided by that time that if Britain wanted in they would get in.\", \"from\": 109, \"to\": 201, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was pretty clear that Britain would probably go in.\", \"from\": 202, \"to\": 256, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Although Britain stood to lose in some ways, one of them being that it would have to contribute a lot of money to the European Community budget to support among other things inefficient German farmers and things like that, people basically felt it would strengthen the British economy and really force the British to undertake some needed economic tuning up of their own.\", \"from\": 258, \"to\": 629, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  Throughout that period the U.S. official policy, and I think it was basically held throughout the government with perhaps some misgivings within some departments, was that we supported further European integration and British entry, the so-called enlargement of the EC.\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 915, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The CIA research office working on the EC usually had a comment at the end of its analyses that said that all of this was looking good and if we do not have European union today, we will certainly have it tomorrow.\", \"from\": 917, \"to\": 1131, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whereas our office would always have a comment, and it was my boss's comment, which would be that you might think it looks like we are heading toward European integration but look out for the French, they will never stand for it.\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1361, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"People were speculating at that time about the possibilities for monetary union.\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There already was a plan.\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The French had put forward the Barre Plan for monetary union.\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1531, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We did point out, and I think rightly so -- I know rightly so -- that full monetary union has tremendous political implications because it certainly restricts freedom of individual countries to run their own fiscal policy, and their own monetary policy and all that entails domestically and politically within each country.\", \"from\": 1533, \"to\": 1856, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At that time also the six member countries of the European Communities were also starting to consult on foreign policy issues.\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 1984, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They did not always speak with one voice but they were beginning to try to do so.\", \"from\": 1985, \"to\": 2066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You were beginning to hear about an EC voice in the United Nations for example.\", \"from\": 2067, \"to\": 2146, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think to some extent within NATO, also.\", \"from\": 2147, \"to\": 2188, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My feeling was that [the European economy] was definitely developing further.\", \"from\": 2189, \"to\": 2266, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They had a customs union by that time.\", \"from\": 2267, \"to\": 2305, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I mean the internal tariff barriers among the six had been removed.\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2373, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They had common external tariffs.\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2407, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They had a common agricultural policy.\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They had a plan for monetary union.They were moving toward a common industrial policy, trying to harmonize their respective company laws, rules on subsidies, etc., and it also looked like they were determined to move ahead on consultations on foreign policy.\", \"from\": 2447, \"to\": 2705, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I felt that it would be a slow process but I felt that it would move forward.\", \"from\": 2706, \"to\": 2783, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2798, \"entities\": []}]}"